name: Abby Goggins
text: Took my daughter for her drivers license today and it was the best experience I’ve ever had at a dmv. Angela was pleasant to work with, quick, friendly and professional. The instructions are a bit confusing, between what’s online, phone recording, and signs posted in the building…but everyone there was helpful and friendly.

name: Amanda Story
text: Online it states they open at 8am. My son and I get over there to get his permit and they tell me "the slots are all full" apparently you have to be there at 6am to fill in a time slot and if you don't get there early enough you're SOL.

name: Aaron Harvey
text: Slow as molasses. Was there at 7 appointment at 9. Called in at 10:30 had stop for worker lunch break with 20 questions left for CDL. Was back at 12:30 waited a while. Had to retake test because it timed out done at 1:20 6 hours 20 mins for CDL. Worker was friendly

name: Justin Martini
text: Went to get information on switching license and registration from out of state. Was told I had to come back at 615 in the morning to get a time slot for the day. Completely ridiculous.

name: Jacqueline Lammon
text: I've lived all over the world and have never waited so long for a driver's license test, renewal or change of address.  It takes days! This office needs more staff and an efficiency expert.

name: Anthony Skin
text: Worst dmv in the state , inefficiently ran  ,and not enough staff went to get the STAR ID put on my license and waited for 5 hours just to be told to come back tomorrow and had to wait 3 more hours at that. Something needs to change!

name: Cyndi Harbison
text: Set there for 2 hours.. after taking off work to go only to be told no more road test for today come back tomorrow...guess they operate under the assumption no one works for a living!!! Some lady was on her third day there... glad to see my tax dollars at work!!!!

name: Kolyn M
text: This is the worst DMV EVER! Picked a number and waited.... another female walks in picked a number sat down and start nagging she’s late for work. She walks into the room and said she’s late for work they sat her down and took care of her. And a few other people who just walks in whom it seemed like their family or friends just by the way they’re talking and laughing... I’ve waited almost two hours till I was finally called.... HORRIBLE DMV EVER!

name: John Hazel
text: Got my star license 4/12/2021 in the old court house.  Be sure you get in the right line, one for star license and one for regular license.  They don’t take checks, need cash or credit/debit.  Bring birth certificate, old license/picture ID and at least two of any of the following: utility bills or insurance card or home insurance policy showing your address.  Wait was about 20 minutes.  Person doing the work was helpful and polite.

name: Meredith Kemp
text: Just needed to pick up a study booklet for my daughter. Examiner guy was awesome and completely friendly. However, the lady working renewals was incredibly rude to me as well as condescending to the poor older gentleman she was helping while we were waiting. I would normally chalk it up to a bad day but this is the second time we’ve had poor interactions with her.

name: D.R. Mikkelsen
text: Great spot to watch the fireworks from, except for the trees and buildings.

name: John Walters
text: they where closed due to some made up holiday every other office was open

name: Melanie Foshee
text: Very kind people... Very quick and easy to get my daughter's license. 😊

name: Loren Jackson
text: Makes it harder for active duty military to renew a license. Somehow it’s my problem that I was shipped overseas and to all points of the globe, all while paying Alabama taxes, only to be told to jump through more hoops to get a new license. I took leave from fighting for our National Security to be sent to another office after showing up at the right office and that office was closed. They literally act like their job is more stressful and more of an inconvenience than being shot at. Thanks.

name: Randy Knowles
text: Paid my property taxes. The personal were very friendly and knowledgeable.

name: Glenn Schmick
text: We have used this DMV over 6 times since we arrived to Alabama last year.  Simply put they have the BEST customer service I have ever seen.  We have moved 16 times in the last 20 years and have dealt with many DMV offices.  There is none better.  They are super friendly, work to solve your challenges and if they are not sure on an answer they will research it and get back to you....I would give them 10 stars!!

name: Dana Hopkins
text: Was in and out within 5 minutes after doors open for business very happy with service

name: Regina or Dolly
text: Must be nice to have a job just to do NOTHING! The lady here made it very difficult for me. Nobody else there for drivers license renewal just me and she made me take a letter and sit down. Probably playing solitaire on her computer finally called me and then tried to act like there was an issue with my address. I do not recommend and this place doesn't deserve 1 star!!!  Needs to be shutdown.

name: Joseph D
text: It was my first time going here and I had to get a state change on my driver's license. The woman working in the left office was more interested in playing on her cell phone than helping me. Not knowing where to get a number, I asked her where they were which judging by her attitude seemed to bother her. I would not recommend going here if you are in need of any assistance.

name: Peachii Clouds
text: I’m not sure where these other reviews are coming from... maybe they had different employees then but the lady who did my renewal was sweet and I had a great experience... only waited maybe 5 mins.

name: Maureen Graham
text: They were fast, friendly and very helpful.  I got my new Alabama Star Drivers License.  Just make sure you bring all necessary documents with you when transferring from another state.

name: Dank Jeri
text: If I could give this a -5 stars I would. Worst experience I've ever had anywhere. Montgomery DMV is worth more than the drive even if you live in the wetumpka area. The most uncoordinated and super u helpful group of officials. Came in for permit and license tests, was told to wait when not directed by any signs on what to do. Waited 2 hours just to be told if there is no numbers you might as well leave by the same person who told me to wait. Complete waste of my time. Renewals shouldn't be done there either, should be done online, you waste everyone's time.

name: Rebecca Brown
text: Got there at 8am Friday morning & was 4th in line. Was done before 9! Person in charge was very helpful and nice. We're military and I was getting my non-resident boat license. Husband also had a good experience on a separate occasion.

name: Kasey //
text:
Where do I even begin.

Trying to get boater licenses and drove here from Montgomery because the Montgomery office wouldn’t issue one to someone with a Texas DL because they don’t know how to do their job. So our friends told us come to Wetumpka. And here we are.

We arrived at 3:30 and an extreeemely rude and unprofessional woman told us it was too late in the day because “he” (who is “he?” The only employee who actually does anything here?) was doing a driver test and didn’t have time for us.

Absolutely freaking ridiculous. It shouldn’t be this difficult to get a damn boating license!

OH, and another gentlemen there who was fed up with the lack of service and professionalism called their phone. We stood and listened for it to ring and it NEVER DID. They probably silenced their phones here to avoid work.

Literally the worst example of government I've ever seen.

name: Josh Dennis
text: They are only open for 7 hours. The actual hours are 8 to 4 but they take a 1 hour lunch break.....I am fairly certain they are suppose to be here until 430 if anyone knows how to report this we need to make that happen. 7 hour work days......yeah I highly doubt it is suppose to be like that.

name: ihatenubs
text: You work at the dmv and only do renewals I get it. But don’t act like you don’t know anything and then just play on your phone.

name: Tiffany Miszkiel
text: This place has never been helpful. They make their own hours and tell you when they can possibly fit you into their schedule.  Not convenient at all.  I have been forced to go to Montgomery on numerous occasions.

name: Nah
text: They WILL NOT answer the phone don't even try

name: Wizard of Om/ Brandon Parker
text: Sorry you all had to wait on the person in front of you and were late to something obviously important enough that you would take out your frustrations on a wonderful establishment. This was my first visit there and it’s on record. After being mad at every dmv I ever walked into because their communication skills were so bad, it was brought to my attention from a friend to go to Wetumpka because of their friendly staff. She was exactly right. I have never felt so taken care of, or for that matter more welcome before in a dmv in my life. They answered my calls, they helped me find out what information I needed, and gave me a written as well as drivers test the same day. Shook my hand on the way out and told me to have a great evening. Why can’t all drivers license offices be more like this one??!!

name: Sarah Sigmon
text: I don't even give this place a ONE star, more like 1/2 a star. They NEVER answer the phone and they are unprofessional.

name: Kelsie Dennis
text: I had to go to Atauga county because apparently Elmore County can change their hours anytime they want and not tell anybody. People already hate getting their license renewed or replaced. There's no sense in making it any more inconvenient than it already is.

name: Kristy Weighall
text: Doesn't even deserve 1 star.

name: ovodollas
text: I sat there today for literally 3 hours waiting to get my drivers license, also they have no public restrooms. The smell in this office was so horrible .

name: Amber Till
text: Great customer service

name: Tanisha Johnson
text: Everytime I call I can't get an answer.

name: Anita Winter
text: Terrible. Not helpful at all.

name: Lavoris Stinson
text: It was my first visit

name: DeLacy Curl
text: Quick, easy, and friendly. I renewed my ID and they had me in and out. Ensure you come with all of your documents and it will be a quick visit.

name: Patricia Macready
text: No line at3 on a Monday afternoon. Quick and easy to get STAR license. Had all my docs with me. Polite and friendly service. ❤️ My City.

name: Douglas Rush
text: Very friendly and fast service.   I needed the Star ID and I was in and out in 30 minutes.  Both women working there are friendly and professional

name: Kirby Thompson
text: Excellent service.  Replaced lost documents.  Friendly folks, very helpful!

name: Shankar V
text: Very helpful staff. Got my job done in less than 2 minutes.

name: Bob Douglas
text: The staff was really friendly.  Made the two hour wait seem not as long.

name: jessie atwell
text: I took my brother in for the written/driver's test. We were in and out in a little over 2 hours. The ladies working were very knowledgeable and kind.

name: Eric Reda
text: Extremely friendly staff, very efficient and quick. Office adheres to CDC COVID guidelines; every one masked and being safe.

name: Robert Davis
text: Wonderful experience, friendly staff

name: DataKiller
text: It does have a wait but it's very clean and the tester's are very courteous.

name: Alex adam
text:
Fast service.
Thank you

name: Andrew Rolfsen
text:
The work ethic at this office is very poor. The lines are always long and they will bump EVERYONE that's been waiting for HOURS to do a driving test. There are usually only one or two people working. They close their office from noon to 1, regardless of whether or not they have people there that have been waiting all morning. It generally takes them 30-45 minutes to process 1 permit.

Good luck getting them to answer their phones. They shut them off.

Here's a hint for whichever department runs this show:
Hire more people or start making the office by appointment only.

name: Frank Rivers
text:
One examination person on duty, if you are not the 1st. 5 people in line before lunch, ..........you're out of luck.
If you are not the 3rd. Person in line after lunch,  ...........you're out of luck.
Limited seating. ...........

name: Stephanie Qrys
text:
Got my "Real" / star ID with relative ease.  Called ahead to make sure I had all the documents needed on hand.  The office was a little understaffed so there was about a 40-minute wait to be seen.  The staff members were friendly and the actual process of getting my license was pretty quick.

The worst part of the trip was the impatient people whining. Patience is a virtue y'all!

name: Marisha G
text:
Absolutely horrible place! I waited three and a half hours to be told I could I couldn't get a license transfer. I verified all my information on the website and with the individual working when I checked in. She told me I was good to go. When it was finally my turn I was told I needed an additional document not listed! After waiting over three hours I was turned away and told to just make an appointment in Montgomery and not wait here again.

This place is unprofessional. There are no clear directions on the site or in the office. They are understaffed with only one person working.

name: Mariah Arnold
text: They never answer the phone and take way too long to get both my permit and license (too different trips, both a hassle).

name: colleen vinti laundry
text: Horrible. Sat there for 2 hours only to have them tell us to come back monday morning at 8am!

name: Bo Byrd
text: The lady at the desk with the long nails was awesome, so I suspect the reason this place has so many bad reviews is because of the other lady; she was the one waddling around who does the road tests - she was awful.

name: Randall Davis
text:
My son was scheduled to do his road test in Birmingham but it was raining and would be all day
We drove down to this location and were amazed. The location was perfect....the lady working was very nice. He was first in line to drive. She explained everything about how he did on the drive. I would never go to the one in Birmingham after visiting this one. Was it worth the drive? I would drive twice as far :)

name: Jim Middlebrooks
text: Real good setup to perform their jobs

name: Kat Astrophe
text: Fast , organized and nice!  Even with high volume!

name: Lindsey Wright
text: Little wait not to bad staff was courteous

name: t nagrom nagrom
text: I was just told  on the phone by an employee, that even though the hours say until 4:30 pm that they could stop processing a 4 pm.  So I guess their hours should read from 8 am until whenever in the $%^# they feel like it.

name: ghost killer
text: It's ok place to get what you need like a ID or driver's license

name: Lindsey Martin
text: officer was pleasant and helpful

name: Everett Brooks
text: Great experience fast friendly service

name: jojo Hunt
text: Needs more staff ......called for 3 hours trying to find out what paperwork was needed....no answer ......got there at 11:15 ......lady behind the desk said i stop taking people at 11 because i close from 12-1 for lunch ......get back up there at 12:40 ......waited for them to open ......opened at 1 ......then set there till 2:30 for a 15 minute test .....then another 20 mins just to print the permit out .....and on top of all this ....there was literally 20 people there that needed to be helped ......i really hope no one was told to come back tomorrow cause it was closing time

name: David Moreno
text: Polite and helpful.

name: Will Moseley
text: They will never answer the phone or call back and when you go in they are rude

name: Grace Kelley
text: Fast and efficient

name: Angel Fagan
text: It's too small for the clientele they provide for and not enough people to serve people in a timely manner. I've been there 3 times and still have yet to get my license transferred

name: Sarah Hunt
text: FYI Go early to get one of the very limited spots. Her lunch is 12 to 1 so if u show up at 11:30 to bad come back after 1. They only do 5 driving tests in the morning and afternoon then they do 10 ID’s after that. That’s ALL they will do. Oh and sign in on the clipboard even though the sign on the door says stop and wait outside.

name: Johnny Huett
text: Great as always

name: Melissa Weaver (sweetmelissa)
text: Was in n out...quickest time I have ever spent at dmv

name: Scott Bishop
text: Dylan got his license

name: Clinshetta Patterson
text: Quick!! Thank you, Ms. Valencia 😁
